Self-nanoemulsifying drug delivery systems is an efficient, elegant, and more patient compliant formulation approach for poorly water soluble drugs. It may enhance drug solubility, dissolution behavior in the GIT, gut permeability and thus may increase the absorption of the poorly water soluble model drug, TAL (
 Elgart et al., 2013; 
 Shakeel et al., 2016). The purpose of the current study was to enhance bioavailability of TAL by designing suitable SNEDDS formulations.
